<taxonomicName id="30A64D65FFFE4B5DFA2B0198FEF97AB4" authorityName="R. L. Zhao, J. X. Li &amp; M. Q. He" authorityYear="2021" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Agaricaceae" genus="Micropsalliota" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="7" pageNumber="174" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="dentatomarginata">
<emphasis id="C5D2EAF4FFFE4B5DFA2B0198FEF97AB4" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="174">M. dentatomarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be easily distinguished in having bigger basidiospores (5.8–6.3 × 3.4–4 μm) and 
<taxonomicName id="30A64D65FFFE4B5DFA8001A4FA0C7AB4" box="[1318,1445,1202,1228]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Agaricaceae" genus="Micropsalliota" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="7" pageNumber="174" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="subalba">
<emphasis id="C5D2EAF4FFFE4B5DFA8001A4FA0C7AB4" box="[1318,1445,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="174">M. subalba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, phylogenetically close to this new species, differ in having broader cheilocystidia (6.8–8 μm) and white to light gray pileus (
<bibRefCitation id="93374B17FFFE4B5DFF7F01EDFDFF7B6C" author="Heinemann, P. &amp; Little Flower, S." box="[217,598,1274,1300]" pageId="7" pageNumber="174" pagination="75 - 84" refId="ref5189" refString="Heinemann, P. &amp; Little Flower, S. (1983) Micropsalliota de Kerala (Inde). Bulletin du Jardin Botanique National de Belgique 53: 75 - 84." type="journal article" year="1983">Heinemann &amp; Little Flower 1983</bibRefCitation>
).
